paragraphs:
[4]
The main issue addressed by the Applicants is whether the Board erred in respect of its credibility finding on the bases that:
1. The Board erred by finding a "misstatement" in respect of his political profile in his Personal Information Form (PIF);
2. The Board's finding of lack of political knowledge on the part of the Applicant was based upon evidence given by the Applicant that was misconstrued or ignored by the Board;
3. The Applicant did include, in his PIF, reference to the collusion of the SLPF and the police; and
4. The Applicant provided a reasonable explanation, supported by an articling student, for omitting the precipitating incident from his interview at the POE.
